<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Jackson Stahlkuppe</strong></span> is currently incarcerated at Central Correctional Institution in Macon, Georgia. His fiction has appeared in the <em>Chattahoochee Review, Snake Nation Review, </em>and<em> Outlaw Biker</em>. He wrote &ldquo;The Banana Hymn,&rdquo; which appears in this issue, in memory of his father.</p><a href="/contributors/jackson-stahlkuppe" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
